ADNEC’s Exhibition Hall which is located in Abu Dhabi, Marina area has been confirmed to reach 40% completion. The 10,000 meters squared hall was also announced by the company to have work proceeding at such a fast pace that the project is two weeks ahead of its scheduled timelines. The Abu Dhabi National Exhibitions Company (ADNEC) is confirmed to have reached a construction milestone with what will be the biggest exhibition hall in North Africa and the Middle East as well. The group CEO and Managing Director of ADNEC, Al Dhaheri, paid for the site of ADNEC’s Exhibition Hall and carried out an inspection of the hall alongside the progress of the project’s construction works. The hall has been scheduled to open later on in the year, estimated to be in October. Read Also Top Mega Projects in UAE (United Arab Emirates) During the visit, Al Dhaheri expressed his excitement in regards to the progress of the project’s construction works. He also acknowledged the fact that the exhibition hall will be the first of its kind in the region, and in effect, will be a valuable asset to ADNEC. The group CEO also revealed that ADNEC’s Exhibition Hall will act as a token of support for Abu Dhabi’s efforts in consolidating its position as a global destination for leisure tourism as well as business tourism. Moreover, he added, ADNEC’s Exhibition Hall will play a major role in contributing to ADNEC’s stance as an influential and grand player in the business tourism sector by the enhancement of the company’s ability to organize and host more major and special international events and exhibitions in all relevant fields. The exhibition hall was described by Al Dhaheri as having a global style that provides a wide spectrum and a distinctive array of services, advanced equipment, and infrastructure alongside several facilities.